</td><td><img src="themes/WebDesignHQ2/images/pixel.gif" width="10" height="1" border="0" alt=""></td><td width="100%">
<center><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#666666"><tr><td>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="8" bgcolor="#333333"><tr><td>
<font class="pn-title">Event Point Distribution</font><br><br><font class="pn-normal">(897 total words in this text)</font><br><font class="pn-normal">(33 Reads)</font> &nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Sections&amp;file=index&amp;req=printpage&amp;artid=2"><img src="modules/Sections/images/print.gif" border="0" Alt="Printer friendly page" width="15" height="11"></a></font><br><br><br><br><font class="pn-normal"><center><b>Events and How Loot Calls Work</b></center>
<br>
<br>
Loot drops during official raids will be based mostly off Event Points (EPs)  
with minimal influence from Officer decision.  Event Points will be assigned  
as follows:
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<br>
<br>
<center><b>EVENT POINT DISTRIBUTION</center></b>
<br>
<br>
Event points will be given out as follows:
<br>
<br>
Raid Time: 2 (or less) hour(s) = 1 EP Per Hour (2)<br>
Raid Time: 4 (or less) hour(s) = 1 EP Per First 2 Hours AND 2 EP Per  
additional Hour<br>
Raid Time: More than 4 hour = 1 EP Per First 2, 2 EP Per Next 2, 4 EP per  
additional.<br>
<br>
<br>
For example:
<br>
<br>
Player X attended a raid for 4 hours and 30 minutes:
<br>
<br>
They receive a total of: (2 * 1) + (2 * 2) + (4 * .5) = 8 EP
<br>
<br>
Also note that members with extra responsibilities (event  
coordinator and member representative) will have a bonus MULTIPLIER applied after total Event  
Points have been determined.
<br>
<br>
<b>NOTE TO DRUIDS/WIZARDS:</b>
<br>
<br>
Any and all druids/wizards who are designated to pick people up and teleport  
them to the event will receive a gratuity of TWO EPs for their time and  
trouble so long as they are around at the end of the event to teleport people  
out as well.
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<br>
<br>
Senior Officers may give out EPs at their discretion for good deeds, superb  
role-playing, and honorary medals of guild membership so long as they have  
another Officer's "OK".  It is the Senior Officers job to notify the Member  
Representative of this so it may properly be recorded and noted.
<br>
<br>
Members will receive EPs per month of guild membership as follows:
<br>
<br>
1 Month................... 1 EP<br>
2 Months................. 3 EP<br>
3 Months................. 6 EP<br>
4 Months................. 14 EPs<br>
5 Months................. 24 EPs<br>
6 Months................. 36 EPs<br>
7 Months................. 50 EPs<br>
8 Months................. 66 EPs<br>
9 Months................. 84 EPs<br>
10 Months.............. 104 EPs<br>
11 Months.............. 126 EPs<br>
12 Months.............. 200 EPs<br><br>
Leader.................... 20 EPs / Month<br>
First Officer........... 20 EPs / Month<br>
Treasurer.............. 30 EPs / Month<br>
Event Coord........... 30 EPs / Month<br>
Member Rep.......... 30 EPs / Month<br>
Class Officer.......... 15 EPs / Month<br>
<br>
<br>
Event Coordinators and Member Representatives will receive EPs same as the members however multiplied by the following:
<br>
<br>
Event Coordinator x 1.5<br>
Member Representative x 1.5<br>
<br>
<br>
These multiples are added to the value due to the fact that these officers  
have extra duties that require more detail and work than a regular member.   
The Event Coordinator and the Member Representative both require a great deal  
of "paper" work, and thus are rewarded by the x2.
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<br>
<br>
EPs only apply to the MAIN character of a player unless a situation (which  
is outlined in the Rules and Regulations) chooses otherwise.  If a player  
wishes to loot an item for their ALTERNATE, they will face a multiple of x2  
the normal cost of EPs for the item.
<br>
<br>
Players are responsible for their time and to report it to the Event  
Coordinator AS WELL AS the Member Representative.  During your arrival to an  
event, it is YOUR RESPONSIBILITY to check in with the previous two people to  
note your attendance.  It is then  YOUR duty to report when you are leaving  
to them.  Any member not notifying the Event Coordinator and the Member  
Representative will forfeit ALL EVENT POINTS for that particular event.  It  
is imperitive that you know this as they will not be reimbursed.  If for some  
reason the Event Coordinator or the Member Representative are not responding  
to you to acknowledge that they received your tell, please notify your CLASS  
OFFICER so they may post on the message board after the event.
<br>
<br>
It is the MEMBER REPRESENTATIVE'S responsibility to post EPs to ALL  
ATTENDING PLAYERS within 48 hours.  If you feel that you, as a member, have  
been neglected, please notify your class officer.  Also, it is STRONGLY  
suggested that you keep track of your times as well.
<br>
<br>
PVP EPs will be assigned per kill shot of an enemy.  If you manage to kill a  
player who is KOS to House of Szat be sure to /guildst them and get a  
screenshot of you killing them.  Points will be given as follows:
<br>
<br>
Enemy Member: 1 EP<br>
Enemy Officer: 3 EP<br>
Enemy Leader: 5 EP<br>
Enemy Leader with logs of him crying about it: 10 EP<br>
Individual KOS: 2 EP<br>
EX-Guild Members who became KOS for any reason: 10 EP<br>
EX-Guild Members who become KOS for any reason AND logs of them crying about  
it: 20 EP<br>
Known Random-PKs: 0 EP<br>
<br>
<br>
As EPs can be given, they can also be taken away.  Any member caught doing  
the following will suffer the following (and/or demotion, warning, suspension  
of attending events, removal from guild):
<br>
<br>
Talking "Shit" in Public Channels: -2 EPs for each infraction<br>
Showing bad "sportsmanship": -1 EP for each infraction<br>
Refusing to follow a valid order: -5 EPs for each infraction<br>
Turning off guild chat: -2 EPs for each infraction<br>
Not having guild tag up when they should: -1 EP for each infraction<br>
Training anyone intentionally: -10 EPs and warning<br>
Corpse camping anyone: -10 EPs and warning<br>
Portal camping anyone: -10 EPs and warning<br>
<br>
<br>
EP's may be transferred to another player at the cost of x2 the giver and  
x1/2 the receiver.  What this means is that if Player X wishes to give Player  
Y 10 EPs, then it will cost Player X 40 EPs for Player Y to receive 10 EPs. (40 / 2 = 20 * .5 = 10)</font></td></tr><tr><td align="center"> &nbsp;&nbsp; <br><br>[ <a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Sections&amp;file=index&amp;req=listarticles&amp;secid=1">Back to Guild Rules and Policies</a> | <a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Sections&amp;file=index&amp;listsections">Sections index</a> ]</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
</center></td><td bgcolor="#000000"><img src="themes/WebDesignHQ2/images/pixel.gif" width=5 height=1 border=0 alt="">
</td></tr></table>
